OL,7,FYet, businesses remained open as usual
OL,8,Fand Antonio Pili, owner of Italian
OL,9,Frestaurant Sapori told ITV Tyne Tees:
OL,10,F"Every sort of business relies on the
OL,11,Fweeks coming up to Christmas to be the
OL,12,Fbusiest time of the year as it gets
OL,13,Fquieter in January.
OL,15,F"You would expect the place to be full
OL,16,Fnow, but it isn't. I expect the
OL,17,Ffootfall to be less and less and less,
OL,18,Fas you know the area is not really
OL,19,Faccessible."
